in the downstairs bathroom.

289
00:23:06,761 --> 00:23:08,881
Then I could've
gotten to it sooner.

290
00:23:33,678 --> 00:23:34,957
CQ...

291
00:23:36,077 --> 00:23:38,957
...this is W-9
GFO. Do you copy?

292
00:23:42,437 --> 00:23:44,636
Dad, this is Ellie. Come back.

293
00:23:47,916 --> 00:23:49,756
This is Eleanor Arroway...

294
00:23:49,996 --> 00:23:52,875
...transmitting
on 14.2 megahertz.

295
00:23:59,315 --> 00:24:00,714
Are you there?

296
00:24:02,834 --> 00:24:04,154
Come back.

297
00:24:10,634 --> 00:24:11,994
Are you there?

298
00:24:13,034 --> 00:24:14,833
Dad, this is Ellie.

299
00:24:46,069 --> 00:24:48,869
Hi, Kent. What are
you doing up so early?

300
00:24:49,948 --> 00:24:51,230
I was thinking...

301
00:24:52,068 --> 00:24:53,988
...we'd make a
pretty good team.

302
00:24:54,628 --> 00:24:58,069
We could put together
an ad hoc SETI program.

303
00:24:58,269 --> 00:25:00,468
You know the Very Large
Array in New Mexico?

304
00:25:00,707 --> 00:25:02,907
It's a dynamite place
to do SETI work...

305
00:25:03,107 --> 00:25:04,826
What are you talking about?

306
00:25:07,147 --> 00:25:08,826
Drumlin pulled the plug.

307
00:25:09,547 --> 00:25:10,507
We're homeless.

308
00:25:24,225 --> 00:25:25,785
It's true, you pulled the plug?

309
00:25:25,985 --> 00:25:28,424
You can't see it now,
but I'm doing you a favor.

310
00:25:28,624 --> 00:25:30,572
You're too promising
a scientist to

311
00:25:30,573 --> 00:25:32,465
waste your gifts
on this nonsense.

312
00:25:32,704 --> 00:25:34,623
I don't consider
what could be...

313
