You're right.

356
00:28:33,363 --> 00:28:34,684
It's crazy.

357
00:28:35,724 --> 00:28:38,203
In fact, it's even
worse than that: nuts!

358
00:28:40,203 --> 00:28:41,603
Want to hear something nutty?

359
00:28:41,763 --> 00:28:44,202
Two guys wanted to build
a thing called an airplane.

360
00:28:44,402 --> 00:28:47,321
People go in it and fly like
birds. Ridiculous, right?

361
00:28:47,562 --> 00:28:49,241
What about breaking
the sound barrier...

362
00:28:49,481 --> 00:28:51,029
...or rockets to the moon, or

363
00:28:51,030 --> 00:28:53,001
atomic energy or
a mission to Mars?

364
00:28:53,242 --> 00:28:54,801
Science fiction, right?

365
00:28:56,521 --> 00:28:58,561
All I'm asking
is for you to just

366
00:28:58,562 --> 00:29:00,480
have the tiniest bit of vision.

367
00:29:00,839 --> 00:29:04,039
To step back and look
at the big picture.

368
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:06,916
Take a chance on
something which could

369
00:29:06,917 --> 00:29:09,240
end up the most
impactful moment...

370
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:11,679
...for humanity,
for the history...

371
00:29:12,279 --> 00:29:13,518
...of history.

372
00:29:17,158 --> 00:29:18,119
I'm sorry.

373
00:29:19,158 --> 00:29:20,718
I just spent 13 months...

374
00:29:21,317 --> 00:29:24,037
...coming into rooms and
talking to people like you.

375
00:29:24,877 --> 00:29:26,198
You're my last chance.

376
00:29:27,597 --> 00:29:29,116
Sorry I wasted your time.

377
00:29:29,317 --> 00:29:29,876
Doctor.

378
00:29:30,718 --> 00:29:31,757
Yes, sir.

379
00:29:43,596 --> 00:29:44,795
You have your money.

380
00:29:47,715 --> 00:29:48,836
Thank you.

381
00:29:50,835 --> 00:29:51,795
Thank you.

382
